    "narrative": "The offensive outlook for Ghost Ride the WHIP centers on the high-upside matchup for **Mickey Moniak**, who earns our daily peak score of 75.75 against Strider. His projection is bolstered by a significant park factor (+14%) and a favorable platoon advantage that capitalizes on his recent momentum. Similarly, **Seiya Suzuki** presents an elite play (73.90) against Merrill Kelly; despite the risk of facing a savvy arm, the combination of a wind-out environment and Kelly\u2019s slow delivery\u2014which invites a higher probability of successful base-stealing attempts\u2014makes **Seiya Suzuki** an essential cog in today's lineup. While **Austin Riley** carries a slightly lower score (67.79) against Kyle Freeland, he remains a \"strong\" start due to the hitters-park boost and a favorable platoon profile that suggests a high ceiling for extra-base hits today.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision involved the marginal utility of **Gabriel Moreno**, who finished with a 51.65 score. **Gabriel Moreno** hovered just below the threshold for the UTIL spot, but ultimately lost out to **Josh Naylor** (54.99). While the optimizer favored **Josh Naylor**\u2019s projected base efficiency, the benching of **Gabriel Moreno** highlights the volatility of our C2 and UTIL spots when facing left-handed starters like Boyd. Meanwhile, we are proceeding with caution regarding **Luis Campusano**, **Vinnie Pasquantino**, **Travis Bazzana**, and **Tyler Soderstrom**; because their official positions remain \"Lineup Pending,\" these efficiency scores are contingent on them maintaining their projected spots in the order. Any significant drop in their batting order will require a reassessment, particularly for **Luis Campusano** and **Travis Bazzana**, who rely on volume to stay above the 50-point mark.\n\nOwners should remain vigilant regarding **Corbin Carroll** and **Dalton Rushing**. Despite their high talent levels, both face headwinds: **Corbin Carroll** is being challenged by Boyd in a wind-out scenario that carries risk, and **Dalton Rushing** is contending with May, whose elite ability to hold runners to a 42% stolen base success rate directly throttles **Dalton Rushing**'s potential value in our scarcity-driven SB format. We will monitor the weather and official lineups closely for **Alex Freeland**, **Brice Turang**, **James Wood**, and the rest of the squad as we look to maximize our limited daily game caps.",
